WBPaper00003166 WBPaper00005462 WBPaper00006010 WBPaper00012991 WBPaper00013229 WBPerson567 2004-06-17 spo-11 mutants are (in the first generation as homozygotes) morphologically normal with a normal amount of fertilized eggs; however, >99.4% of these F2 mutant zygotes die as embryos, and most of the survivors die as newly hatched L1 larvae; and half of those rare F2 mutants that reach adulthood are male, implying that chromosomal disjunction during meiosis is significantly defective and that the mass lethality may be due to embryonic aneuploidy.
